RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 72. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 23500. FOR (REGISTERED BRED AND/OR FOALED IN ILLINOIS) THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING 10,000 FOR HORSES THAT HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 24 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Claiming Races For $7,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BUREAU vied for the early lead from between rivals, gradually angled in approaching the end of two furlongs, had the rail on the bend, battled through the lane, edged ahead under urging inside the last eighth then held TRUIST back under a hand ride. TRUIST broke alertly, was challenged from both sides after a furlong, fought gamely two wide in the stretch but had to settle for second best. ON THE MONEY RED overcame a step slow start to dispute the pace from outside, was three wide through the bend, lacked the extra needed the last three-sixteenths but proved easily best of the others. U S HONOUR NAP in contention from inside, angled out nearing the quarter pole, came into the lane from path four and flattened out. I'M YOUR VALENTINE was in hand behind traffic shortly after leaving the chute, did not keep up two wide on the turn, swung out widest for the drive and had little to offer.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 8000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 24 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GREAT PLAINES took the lead into the first bend, showed the way just off the rail in hand, was let out on the second turn, put to urging with two furlongs to go, widened command under urging in the lane and proved much the best while kept to task to the wire. OKLAHOMA HEAT was settled early running widest, picked up his pace after a half mile, stayed in path three through the second bend, took over second inside the last eighth and gradually opened up on the rest. ARGYBARGY BUCK settled just off the inside, commenced his bid into the stretch, altered out four wide inside the final furlong and caught COPPER CROSSING for third in the waning yards. COPPER CROSSING chased from path three, moved clear for second just off the rail on the second turn but could not sustain his bid in the stretch. I CAN'T TELL YA was a contender from inside for a half mile then steadily yielded along the rail. INDEFENSIBLE chased from inside or just off the rail and showed little.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 56. Claiming Purse 8000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 24 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NOT TO BE DENIED a step slow at the break, responded to advance along the rail, commenced her bid from inside on the bend, took a clear lead upper stretch and maintained control. OH LA DE DA in contention just outside NOT TO BE DENIED, did not keep up two wide on the turn, came into the lane behind the latter, was forced to wait for a clear path, got through just off the inside nearing the sixteenth marker, moved clear for second but could only make up minor ground on the leader. ROARINGLIKETHUNDER pressed the early speed from just outside, was three wide on the bend, fanned outside DELTA LADY entering the lane, drifted out briefly upper stretch, was straightened, lacked a serious late bid but caught the latter for third. DELTA LADY prominent from outside, went for the lead four wide on the turn, angled in beside CESSO nearing the end of a half mile and slowly yielded for the drive. CESSO set a pressured pace between rivals on the backstretch, was challenged from outside on the bend and flattened out in the stretch. MAZLAN angled in midway on the backstretch and faded three wide on the turn. UNEEKY was a brief contender but gave way widest on the bend.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 60. Claiming Purse 8000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 24 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MINI DRESS in contention early just off the inside, waited for room on the bend, squeezed through three wide between rivals leaving the turn and moved clear inside the last furlong. WARM BEAUTY broke somewhat slowly, trailed, staying well off the inside, commenced her bid while widest through the turn, moved clear for second inside the final eighth but could only make up minor ground on the leader in the waning yards. LORI ATTACK pressed the early pace, was three wide on the bend, was forced out and steadied leaving the turn, lacked a significant late bid but edged ahead for third. AMARI S. was hustled to contest the pace between horses, did not keep up two wide on the bend, floated out some leaving the turn, bumped LORI ATTACK and continued to gradually yield. VIVA VIOLENCE vied for the early lead from inside, moved ahead on the turn, floated out some leaving the turn and began to wear down. SENORITA AURORA hesitated and made a leap from the gate, came into contention along the rail on the bend but flattened out the last furlong. RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 5 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 10500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 24 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Claiming Races For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AWESOME WILLY was sent to the lead, angled in entering the first bend, allowed to relax on the backstretch, let out some on the second turn, put to urging entering the lane, steadily opened up on the rest and was kept to task until the final forty yards. TWO COOKIE RULE broke a bit inward, advanced two wide to vie for the lead midway on the backstretch, did not stay with AWESOME WILLYT on the second bend, was no match for the latter when set down for the drive but was unchallenged for second. SUPER SILVER bumped at the break, was settled outside, picked up his pace after a half mile, progressed along the rail on the second turn, swung out three wide into the lane, drifted out as he moved clear for third upper stretch, was corrected with a furlong left and finished evenly. LASTFORTINOFAMILY a step slow at the start, was sent up between rivals, did not stay close through the first bend and only improved position slightly while just off the inside in the stretch. MEMORY BANK angled in some when crowded by TWO COOKIE RULE at the start, bumped SUPER SILVER, was settled and soon far back of the rest and only passed outside tired ones in the lane. READTHETRANSCRIPT was checked briefly when AWESOME WILLY took his path into the first turn, pressed the latter from outside for a half mile then steadily faded. CAMARGO was checked behind traffic into the first bend and steadily gave way from inside once on the backstretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 92. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 16000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD NON-WINNERS OF TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, WAIVER CLAIMING, STARTER OR IBF OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $10,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 24 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Claiming Races For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: D' YANK raced in the second flight between horses on the backstretch, commenced his bid three wide on the bend, angled in some at the quarter pole, was forced out by TAP'S BIG SHOT a couple times as he battled for the lead in the lane and edged ahead in time. PAPA ROCKET slow and somewhat awkward at the start, found his stride after the first sixteenth of a mile, angled out to be three wide as he came into contention on the turn, altered in for a clear path upper stretch, vied for the lead inside the final furlong and was outfinished. TONYS MORNING LINE broke on top, was bumped off stride leaving the chute, settled outside in the second flight, went for the lead four wide on the bend, was forced out a bit wider a couple times in the stretch, rallied belatedly but caught TAP'S BIG SHOT for third near the wire. TAP'S BIG SHOT was hustled along to dispute the early pace while just off the inside, moved ahead on the turn, drifted out some upper stretch, was soon challenged from both sides, drifted out again briefly inside the final furlong and did not have enough left in the waning yards. GIRLOLAMO'GLORY chased from well off the inside, lost ground through the bend and also rallied belatedly in the lane. MAC PANDOWDY forwardly placed inside, gave way the last eighth. FULL MAGAZINE displayed early speed outside TAP'S BIG SHOT, began to yield two wide on the turn, was checked when D' YANK took his path at the quarter pole then steadily gave way. There was a stewards' inquiry into PAPA ROCKET'S start and an objection lodged by the rider of FULL MAGAZINE alleging interference from D' YANK at the quarter pole. After their review, there was no action taken by the stewards regarding either incident.
